import numpy as np
import pyspark.pandas as ps

import pyspark.sql.functions as F
import pyspark.sql.types as T
from pyspark.sql.window import Window

def subscription_filter_data(df):
    
    # Dropping costs that isn't attached to a subscription and is older than a year
    drop_value = '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000'
    one_year_ago = F.date_sub(F.current_date(), 365)
    filtered_df = df.filter((F.col('SubscriptionId') != drop_value) & (F.col('Date') >= one_year_ago))
    
    return filtered_df

def wbs_filter_data(df):

    # Filter away Null-values
    one_year_ago = F.date_sub(F.current_date(), 365)
    filtered_df = df.filter(F.col('ActiveWBS').isNotNull() & (F.col('Date') >= one_year_ago))

    return filtered_df

def anomaly_detection_classifier(df,
                                 filter_column_1, 
                                 filter_column_2, 
                                 cost_column, 
                                 window_size=30):

    
    # Selecting the filter-categories (Subscription and Meter Category), the time-stamp and the cost data
    subscription_costs_by_dates = df.select(filter_column_1, filter_column_2, 'Date', cost_column)

    # Setting a partition window to divide the dataset in the filter options and order it by the Date
    windowSpec = Window.partitionBy(filter_column_1, filter_column_2).orderBy('Date').rowsBetween(-window_size, 0)

    # Set a moving average that is set by the n previous days
    subscription_costs_by_dates = subscription_costs_by_dates.withColumn('MovingAverage', F.avg(F.col(cost_column)).over(windowSpec))

    # Set a moving standard deviation of the same period
    subscription_costs_by_dates = subscription_costs_by_dates.withColumn('MovingStdDev', F.stddev(F.col(cost_column)).over(windowSpec))

    # Set upper thresholds with a standard deviation multiplied by 'n' higher than the moving average
    subscription_costs_by_dates = subscription_costs_by_dates.withColumn('1StdDev', F.col('MovingAverage') + F.col('MovingStdDev'))
    subscription_costs_by_dates = subscription_costs_by_dates.withColumn('2StdDev', F.col('MovingAverage') + (F.col('MovingStdDev') * 2))
    subscription_costs_by_dates = subscription_costs_by_dates.withColumn('3StdDev', F.col('MovingAverage') + (F.col('MovingStdDev') * 3))

    # If the cost is more than the threshold set, then set the datapoint to be 1, otherwise 0
    subscription_costs_by_dates = subscription_costs_by_dates.withColumn('Above_1std', F.when(F.col(cost_column) > F.col('1StdDev'), F.lit(1))\
                                                                                        .otherwise(F.lit(0)))

    # If the cost is more than the threshold set, then set the datapoint to be 1, otherwise 0
    subscription_costs_by_dates = subscription_costs_by_dates.withColumn('Above_2std', F.when(F.col(cost_column) > F.col('2StdDev'), F.lit(1))\
                                                                                        .otherwise(F.lit(0)))

    # If the cost is more than the threshold set, then set the datapoint to be 1, otherwise 0
    subscription_costs_by_dates = subscription_costs_by_dates.withColumn('Above_3std', F.when(F.col(cost_column) > F.col('3StdDev'), F.lit(1))\
                                                                                        .otherwise(F.lit(0)))

    return subscription_costs_by_dates

file_path = "abfss://usage@s037costmgmt.dfs.core.windows.net/exports/monthly/ACMMonthlyAmortizedCost/*/Extended_v2_ACMMonthlyAmortizedCost_*.parquet"

df = spark.read.format('parquet').load(file_path).select('SubscriptionId',
                                                         'MeterCategory',
                                                         'ActiveWBS',
                                                         'Date',
                                                         'EffectivePrice',
                                                         'CostInBillingCurrency')

filtered_subs_df = subscription_filter_data(df)

subscription_costs_by_dates = anomaly_detection_classifier(df=filtered_subs_df,
                                                           filter_column_1='SubscriptionId',
                                                           filter_column_2='MeterCategory',
                                                           cost_column='CostInBillingCurrency',
                                                           window_size=30)

display(subscription_costs_by_dates)

filtered_wbs_df = wbs_filter_data(df)

wbs_costs_by_dates =  anomaly_detection_classifier(df=filtered_wbs_df,
                                                   filter_column_1='ActiveWBS',
                                                   filter_column_2='MeterCategory',
                                                   cost_column='CostInBillingCurrency',
                                                   window_size=30)

display(wbs_costs_by_dates)

calculation_type = ['ACMMonthlyAmortizedCost', 'ACMMonthlyActualCost']

for calc in calculation_type:
    source_path = f"abfss://usage@s037costmgmt.dfs.core.windows.net/exports/monthly/{calc}/*/Extended_v2_{calc}_*.parquet"

    print(f"Reading data from: {source_path}")
    df = spark.read.format('parquet').load(source_path)
    
    print("Filtering raw data by subscription")
    filtered_df = subscription_filter_data(df)

    print("Running the Anomaly Detection Classifier for Subscription-partitioned data")
    subscription_costs_by_dates =  anomaly_detection_classifier(df=filtered_df,
                                                                filter_column_1='SubscriptionId',
                                                                filter_column_2='MeterCategory',
                                                                cost_column='CostInBillingCurrency',
                                                                window_size=30)

    print('Filtering raw data by WBS')
    filtered_wbs_df = wbs_filter_data(df)

    print("Running the Anomaly Detection Classifier for WBS-partitioned data")
    wbs_costs_by_dates =  anomaly_detection_classifier(df=filtered_wbs_df,
                                                       filter_column_1='ActiveWBS',
                                                       filter_column_2='MeterCategory',
                                                       cost_column='CostInBillingCurrency',
                                                       window_size=30)


    subscription_destination_path = f"abfss://usage@s037costmgmt.dfs.core.windows.net/anomaly_detection/{calc}_AnomalyDetection_Subscriptions.parquet"
    wbs_destination_path = f"abfss://usage@s037costmgmt.dfs.core.windows.net/anomaly_detection/{calc}_AnomalyDetection_WBS.parquet"
    
    print(f"Writing Subscription-partitioned classification data to this path: {subscription_destination_path}")
    subscription_costs_by_dates.write.format('parquet').mode('overwrite').save(subscription_destination_path)
    print('Write Complete!')

    print(f"Writing WBS-partitioned classification data to this path: {subscription_destination_path}")
    wbs_costs_by_dates.write.format('parquet').mode('overwrite').save(wbs_destination_path)
    print('Write Complete!')
    print("-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------")
    print(' ')
